subjective.presenting_complaint: Headaches for the past 2 weeks, initially intermittent but now daily
subjective.history_of_presenting_illness: Headaches started 2 weeks ago, initially intermittent but now daily lasting a few hours to most of the day. Describes them as a dull pressure on both sides of the head, worse with prolonged computer use.
subjective.associated_symptoms: Sometimes feels tired and sensitive to light when headaches are bad.
subjective.explicit_negatives: No nausea, vomiting, vision changes, head injury, recent illness, fever, medical conditions, or regular medications. No weakness, numbness, difficulty speaking, or balance problems.

assessment.working_diagnosis: Tension-type headaches likely related to posture, screen time, and stress. No red flag symptoms suggesting something more serious.

plan.management_advice: Advised regular breaks from screens, good hydration, regular meals, improving sleep, and relaxation/posture exercises. Over-the-counter pain relief ok if needed but try to limit to avoid rebound headaches.
plan.follow_up_or_safety_netting: Follow up in a few weeks if no improvement and consider further investigation if needed. Seek medical help if headaches worsen suddenly, develop new symptoms like vomiting, visual changes, weakness or confusion.
